c: 13
v: 16
t: "Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho is the Lord of the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúGod!‚ÄĚ Ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúWhy ňĻthenňļ have you taken besides Him lords who cannot even benefit or protect themselves?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúCan the blind and the sighted be equal? Or can darkness and light be equal?‚ÄĚ¬†Or have they associated with God partners who ňĻsupposedlyňļ produced a creation like His, leaving them confused between the two creations? Say, ‚ÄúGod is the Creator of all things, and He is the One, the Supreme.‚ÄĚ"